The Herald The driver of this truck underestimated the height of the Seke Flyover bridge forcing the vehicle to fall and land on its side last night partially blocking the road. This caused heavy congestion this morning with vehicle queues stretching as far as the Coca-Cola corner in Granite Side. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-502337" src="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2020/08/5-2.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2020/08/5-2.jpg 680w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2020/08/5-2-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" />  <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-502339" src="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2020/08/6-1.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2020/08/6-1.jpg 680w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2020/08/6-1-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" />